        "System.Description": "<div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br><span style=\"display:inline !important;\"><span style=\"display:inline !important;\">After submitting scanned checks on the vsoft scan check dialog zeus screen does not populate totals in the credit amount and checks in fields.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"display:inline !important;\"></span></span></div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></div></div><div><br></div><div>1- Add Scan Bond Button in GL Credit transaction for adjustment during day 2 process\n<br></div>2.This scans the bond image but processes as a check, so it will not recalculate the Redemption value and will not generate a 1099 report.\n<br>3-This requires VSoft provides a Bond mode 3 functionality which is scanning a Bond as a check.\n<br><br>There is a Vsoft part to this enhancement request as well. \n<br><br>This will be a denorm and .dll fix. <hr>Reporter: Mohammed Mohiuddin<hr>External ID: 1912<hr>Components: <hr>Affiliates affected: NBA,NSB,VBC,ZFNB,ABT,CBT<hr>Original assignee: Trung Thai<hr>Found with a Test Case",
        "Microsoft.VSTS.TCM.SystemInfo": "<div>Zeus Teller&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Miscellaneous -&gt; GL Credit Transaction</div><div><br></div>",
        "Microsoft.VSTS.TCM.ReproSteps": "<div>1- Launch GL Credit Tranasaction</div><div>2- Select GL account from drop down and enter serial number</div><div>3- Click Scan button</div><div>4- Scan Checks&nbsp;</div><div>5- Submit on the Vsoft screen</div><div><br></div><div>Result: Zeus screen does not populate totals in the credit amount and checks in fields.&nbsp;</div>",
        "System.Tags": "ALL AFFILIATES; ZEUS-8081"
    },
